main event: A witness in Bolivar, Ohio reported seeing a white object the size of a dime in the sky on October 14, 1966 for about 2.5 minutes.
interesting points: The object moved in a varied course and gradually disappeared.
The witness could not determine the speed or distance of the object.
The witness was outdoors in a rural area when the sighting occurred.
The witness reported the sighting, but additional information was requested to evaluate the case.
The report includes sketches and diagrams to illustrate the sighting, but no photographs were provided.
sighted object: a white object the size of a dime
